    "Size of the multiplet: Line operators furnishing the 1-charge ρ (2) lie in a multiplet M L, with total number of lines in M L beingn:= Size of the multiplet M L = Number of right cosets of H L in G (0).",
    "(25)The multiplet is irreducible in the sense that we can obtain any line L ′ ∈ M L from any other line L ∈ M L by acting by some element g ∈ G (0).",
    "The size n of M L is known as the dimension of the 2-representation ρ (2).2.",
